Fuck, he's a big, old boy.

30:57.654 --> 31:00.782
Do you need anything?
Let me get you a rag.

31:00.890 --> 31:03.358
Maybe a couple of those aspirin.

31:12.535 --> 31:15.333
Can I... Can I have a couple for my tooth?

31:23.780 --> 31:25.680
Thanks for helping me.

31:25.782 --> 31:27.977
I didn't really do anything.

31:29.219 --> 31:31.210
Where'd you go?

31:32.055 --> 31:34.114
I woke up, and I thought...

31:34.424 --> 31:37.416
I went to get us some food.

31:37.527 --> 31:40.223
I hope you don't mind I took the key.

31:40.330 --> 31:42.594
No, that's all right.

31:44.467 --> 31:46.958
Who was that guy?

31:48.071 --> 31:50.835
My ex. He's a nut.

31:52.475 --> 31:54.943
Would you maybe make me
a vodka and coke?

31:55.044 --> 31:57.205
I don't have to work tonight.

32:05.555 --> 32:07.523
How long were you married?

32:09.659 --> 32:12.389
Long enough to still get scared at night.

32:12.495 --> 32:14.963
- Do you have any kids?
- No.

32:38.288 --> 32:40.415
I don't like that guy.

32:40.523 --> 32:42.582
I don't like that he hit you.

32:44.127 --> 32:46.425
I can't say I'm wild about it myself.

32:48.364 --> 32:50.832
He said he's coming back here.

32:50.934 --> 32:52.834
Eventually.

32:52.936 --> 32:54.904
Maybe you need some kind of security.

32:55.004 --> 32:57.734
I can take care of myself.

32:57.840 --> 33:00.331
Why do you get scared at night?

33:00.443 --> 33:04.675
- I was just kidding.
- You should be scared.

33:04.781 --> 33:06.908
How come?

33:07.016 --> 33:10.383
People can do things to you,
things you don't even know about.

33:11.487 --> 33:12.954
Like what?

33:13.056 --> 33:16.651
They try to control you.
They try to force you to act a certain way.

33:16.759 --> 33:18.920
They can drive you crazy, too.

33:27.770 --> 33:31.934
I shouldn't talk about it.
I don't know if it's safe or not.

33:32.976 --> 33:35.911
- I think we're pretty safe here.
- No.

33:36.012 --> 33:38.776
Not really. You're never really safe.

33:40.283 --> 33:43.275
One time, maybe, a long time ago,
people were safe,

33:43.386 --> 33:45.479
but that's all over.

33:45.588 --> 33:47.715
Not anymore, not on this planet.

33:47.824 --> 33:50.452
We'll never really be safe again.

33:50.560 --> 33:55.224
We can't be, not with all the technology,
the chemicals, the information.

33:56.866 --> 33:59.334
Well, I don't like to think about that.

34:00.670 --> 34:04.003
Sometimes, though,
when you're lying in bed at night,

34:05.441 --> 34:07.705
you can feel it...

34:08.678 --> 34:12.444
All the machines,
people working their machines,

34:12.547 --> 34:14.743
the works, humming.

34:16.452 --> 34:19.909
I don't like to go on about it,
'cause it freaks people out.

34:20.023 --> 34:23.186
I wish I didn't think about it either,
but they don't let you forget.

34:23.293 --> 34:25.784
They want you to know they're there.

34:25.895 --> 34:27.726
That what's there?

34:27.830 --> 34:29.764
The machines?

34:31.134 --> 34:33.931
Nothing makes them happier
than knowing people are aware

34:34.036 --> 34:36.266
the machines are up and running.

34:42.145 --> 34:44.079
That's some pretty wild shit.

34:44.179 --> 34:47.047
Yeah, I know you hate me.

34:47.150 --> 34:48.617
You think I hate you?

34:49.819 --> 34:51.650
- I don't know.
- I don't hate you.

34:51.754 --> 34:53.312
Okay.

34:55.190 --> 34:57.056
Why do you think I hate you?

34:57.160 --> 34:59.424
I don't know.

34:59.529 --> 35:03.124
I wouldn't let you stay here if I hated you.

35:03.232 --> 35:06.360
Yeah, I guess that's right, unless...

35:06.469 --> 35:08.699
Yeah, I guess that's right.

35:08.871 --> 35:12.307
- Well, we're friends.
- We are?

35:12.408 --> 35:17.243
I don't have a lot of friends,
but the ones I have, I'm real good to.

35:17.347 --> 35:19.315
But you don't trust me.

35:20.783 --> 35:22.375
Why do you say that?

35:23.319 --> 35:25.981
You lied to me about having children.

35:29.659 --> 35:31.991
How'd you know that?

35:32.095 --> 35:34.723
I told you, I pick up on stuff.

35:36.432 --> 35:40.129
Well, I didn't lie.

35:40.236 --> 35:43.000
I don't have children. I had one.

35:43.973 --> 35:45.702
What happened?

35:45.808 --> 35:48.971
- I lost him.
- He died?

35:51.414 --> 35:53.245
No, he disappeared.

35:53.349 --> 35:55.317
Really?

35:55.418 --> 35:58.512
Yeah, in a grocery store, nine...

36:00.456 --> 36:02.947
10 years ago now.

36:03.059 --> 36:05.653
How old was he?

36:05.762 --> 36:07.320
Six.

36:09.365 --> 36:11.765
Do you have any more questions?
'Cause if you do, ask them now.

36:11.868 --> 36:14.029
I don't wanna talk about it again.

36:16.005 --> 36:18.371
What was his name?

36:20.943 --> 36:22.740
Lloyd.

36:24.280 --> 36:28.080
When did you stop looking for him?

36:28.184 --> 36:31.017
Couple of years ago.

36:31.120 --> 36:34.453
Except in my sleep.
I still look for him in my sleep.

36:34.557 --> 36:37.082
- Do you ever...
- No.

36:41.164 --> 36:43.792
I did lie about one thing.

36:46.035 --> 36:49.527
I do get scared at night.

36:49.639 --> 36:52.665
If you want, you can...

36:52.775 --> 36:54.970
You can stay here again.

36:56.879 --> 36:58.471
Okay.

36:59.515 --> 37:03.645
It's kind of nice having
somebody around, you know?

37:03.753 --> 37:05.721
Different.

37:15.998 --> 37:20.162
I haven't been to bed with a woman
for a long time,

37:20.269 --> 37:22.897
but I think I could go to bed with you.

37:38.387 --> 37:40.355
Come here, boy.

39:21.624 --> 39:24.525
Motherfucker. Fuck!

39:24.627 --> 39:27.755
- Fuck, fuck, fuck, fuck!
- What's the matter?

39:27.863 --> 39:30.354
Fucking bug! A fucking bug bite!

39:30.466 --> 39:33.594
- A bug?
- Where are you, little motherfucker?

39:33.703 --> 39:36.638
- What kind of bug?
- Look at these bites.

39:39.875 --> 39:42.173
Jesus, those look like spider bites.

39:42.278 --> 39:44.337
Well, I felt it a second ago.

39:44.447 --> 39:47.007
It's like a bedbug or some shit.

39:47.116 --> 39:49.744
- Maybe you killed it.
- No, I had it between my fingers,

39:49.852 --> 39:51.820
but it squiggled out.

39:56.125 --> 39:58.252
Pull back the sheet and find it.

40:05.668 --> 40:08.762
Ah, little fucker!
I was just about to fall asleep.

40:08.871 --> 40:11.066
I don't see it.

40:11.173 --> 40:12.435
- There.
- What?

40:12.541 --> 40:14.202
Right there.

40:14.310 --> 40:17.177
- Where?
- There.

40:17.413 --> 40:19.438
- Where?
- There. You see it?

40:19.548 --> 40:22.142
- What?
- Right there.

40:22.251 --> 40:25.516
- This?
- No. This. That there.

40:25.621 --> 40:28.021
- Well...
- There! Right there, Agnes!

40:28.124 --> 40:30.058
- It's right there!
- Don't get all upset.

40:30.159 --> 40:32.821
- But do you see it?
- Well, I don't know.

40:32.928 --> 40:35.055
Right there.

40:35.164 --> 40:37.428
It's really small.

40:37.533 --> 40:39.694
Well, I guess. What is that?

40:39.802 --> 40:41.235
It's a fucking bug.

40:41.337 --> 40:43.965
No, I know that. What kind of bug?

40:45.141 --> 40:47.803
- Like an aphid.
- An aphid?

40:47.910 --> 40:51.073
An aphid is like a, a...

40:53.449 --> 40:56.043
- A bedbug?
- No.

40:56.152 --> 40:58.416
Well, yeah, kind of. More like a louse.

40:58.521 --> 41:02.184
- Louse? Oh, lice.
- Not like head lice. More like plant lice.

41:02.291 --> 41:05.192
- Oh, like a termite.
- No, that's more like a thrip.

41:05.294 --> 41:07.728
- "Thrip"?
- Like a termite.

41:07.830 --> 41:10.492
- You mean "tick"?
- No, a tick's like a flea.

41:10.599 --> 41:12.829
A thrip's like a termite.

41:12.935 --> 41:15.233
- What's a bedbug like?
- A bedbug.

41:15.337 --> 41:17.567
No, I mean, what is a bedbug?

41:17.673 --> 41:19.664
A bedbug.

41:19.775 --> 41:22.437
I thought that was a nickname.

41:22.545 --> 41:25.343
- This is an aphid.
- A plant lice?

41:25.448 --> 41:28.474
- I think so.
- And they bite?

41:28.584 --> 41:31.348
This one sure did.

41:31.454 --> 41:33.820
Well, maybe it's not really
an orchid or whatever.

41:33.923 --> 41:36.721
- Aphid.
- Oh, aphid fucking schmafid.

41:36.826 --> 41:41.195
Whatever. Could you just kill it
so I can get some sleep?

41:41.297 --> 41:44.391
- Fucker.
- Oh, that showed him.

41:44.500 --> 41:46.695
- Hold on. Get up.
- How come?

41:46.802 --> 41:49.930
- There might be more.
- There's not. We would've seen them.

41:50.039 --> 41:52.940
- You almost didn't see that one.
- Well, it was very small.

41:53.042 --> 41:55.875
That's my point, Agnes. They're small.
We may not have seen them.

41:55.978 --> 41:58.469
Oh, Jesus!

41:58.581 --> 42:02.039
Look at my wrist. You wanna wake up
in the morning and find this?

42:03.586 --> 42:05.554
It's morning, and now I am awake.

42:05.654 --> 42:07.417
Sort of.

42:08.691 --> 42:11.819
- Do they travel in packs or something?
- "Packs"?

42:11.927 --> 42:18.298
Well, if there's one, do you have reason to
suspect there's others with them?

42:18.400 --> 42:21.460
Makes sense.
And you're assuming it's a "him"...

42:21.570 --> 42:23.561
Some rogue aphid on his travels

42:23.672 --> 42:27.836
instead of some matriarchal type
with a big brood somewhere.

42:27.943 --> 42:30.537
- "Matriarchal"?
- You ever watch "Big Valley"?

42:30.646 --> 42:32.807
- Sure.
- Barbara Stanwyck?

42:34.016 --> 42:35.278
Like her.

42:38.320 --> 42:40.584
Where'd you learn to talk like that anyway?

42:40.689 --> 42:42.554
School.

42:42.658 --> 42:45.752
- I was home-schooled.
- No shit?

42:45.861 --> 42:48.591
My father didn't believe in school.

42:48.697 --> 42:52.633
Must've done a pretty good job,
throwing around words like "matriarchal."

42:52.735 --> 42:55.260
Well, I learned that from "Big Valley".

42:56.906 --> 42:58.373
This is clean.

43:01.677 --> 43:03.804
You got a nice body.

43:05.114 --> 43:07.173
So do you.

43:07.283 --> 43:09.945
Better looking without clothes on it.

43:10.052 --> 43:12.452
I agree.

43:12.555 --> 43:15.683
You know how some people look nice,
and then you see them naked

43:15.791 --> 43:17.691
and they're a big disappointment?

43:17.793 --> 43:19.420
Yeah.

43:21.730 --> 43:25.393
Why'd you say you weren't
one for the ladies?

43:25.501 --> 43:26.798
It's true.

43:28.003 --> 43:30.096
Could've fooled me.

43:31.407 --> 43:32.999
You're different.

43:33.876 --> 43:35.844
How am I different?

43:37.346 --> 43:39.906
You don't...

43:40.015 --> 43:42.176
You don't speak the codes.

43:42.284 --> 43:45.515
How long has it been since
you was with a woman?

43:45.621 --> 43:48.749
I don't know. A few years, I guess.

43:48.858 --> 43:50.621
Must've gotten a bad one.

43:50.726 --> 43:53.957
No. I just decided
it wasn't worth it anymore.

43:56.532 --> 44:00.059
- What wasn't?
- You have a center, right?

44:00.169 --> 44:02.194
I mean...

44:02.304 --> 44:07.298
A place inside of you that's just you,
that hasn't been spoiled.

44:07.409 --> 44:11.903
And I think it's really important to try and
keep that space sacred.

44:12.014 --> 44:14.278
In some sense. On some level.

44:14.383 --> 44:17.284
But sex or relationships

44:17.386 --> 44:19.547
cloud that space.

44:19.655 --> 44:21.919
Or they cloud me, I guess,

44:22.024 --> 44:23.651
and make it difficult to be just me,

44:23.759 --> 44:26.887
and not have to worry about

44:26.996 --> 44:29.055
being somebody else.

44:31.467 --> 44:34.436
I sound like a big asshole, don't I?

44:36.038 --> 44:38.029
Not at all.

44:39.575 --> 44:41.736
I like hearing you talk.

44:53.255 --> 44:55.917
- Aren't you gonna answer it?
- No.

44:56.025 --> 44:57.925
- Why not?
- It's Goss.

44:58.027 --> 45:00.120
You were Goss once.

45:02.498 --> 45:03.965
Hello?

45:06.268 --> 45:07.735
Hello?

45:13.208 --> 45:16.075
- Goss, right?
- I don't think so.

45:16.178 --> 45:17.975
What'd they say?

45:18.080 --> 45:20.048
Just static.

45:24.653 --> 45:26.814
- There you go. See?
- Where?

45:26.922 --> 45:29.152
- There.
- I'm sorry. Where?

45:29.258 --> 45:30.885
- Right there.
- Squish him.

45:30.993 --> 45:35.760
There you go again. How do you know
it's not the super-mother aphid,

45:35.864 --> 45:37.525
and she's carrying a million eggs?

45:37.633 --> 45:40.534
Oh! What are plant lice doing in my place?

45:40.636 --> 45:43.127
Biting me, for one thing.

45:43.238 --> 45:46.036
You know what?
I got to get this place sprayed.

45:46.141 --> 45:48.473
I'll do it. I'll buy some stuff tomorrow.

45:48.577 --> 45:51.375
Fuck that. It's their room.
They should pay for it.

45:51.480 --> 45:56.008
- But someone would have to come in.
- Goddamn right, they will.

45:56.118 --> 45:58.348
Well, you do what you want, but I wouldn't.

45:58.454 --> 45:59.682
How come?

46:01.557 --> 46:04.492
- Never mind.
- No, wait. How come?

46:04.593 --> 46:07.153
No, I shouldn't say anything.
It's your place and I don't want to interfere.

46:07.262 --> 46:10.595
Why wouldn't I want someone in my place?
'Cause you're a con?

46:11.500 --> 46:12.831
Why didn't you just tell me when I asked?

46:12.935 --> 46:17.565
I've never been to prison.
I've just got people after me, that's all.

46:17.673 --> 46:20.107
Oh, you've just got people after you.
Well, who?

46:20.209 --> 46:22.268
- I don't want to drag you into it.
- Drag me into what?

46:22.378 --> 46:23.436
Agnes, please.

46:23.545 --> 46:25.308
- I'm not comfortable telling you.
- Drag me into what?

46:25.414 --> 46:27.905
You don't trust me?

46:28.017 --> 46:30.451
- You can trust me. I'm not gonna...
- I trust you. That's not it.

46:30.552 --> 46:34.181
- I don't want you to get hurt.
- I'll take my chances.

46:34.289 --> 46:36.484
I won't.

46:36.592 --> 46:39.186
So, what, you're going?

46:39.294 --> 46:41.854
Where? You don't even got nowhere to go.

46:41.964 --> 46:43.625
I'll be fine.

46:43.732 --> 46:46.394
Oh, well, all right, then. Just fuck you!

46:48.303 --> 46:50.794
You know what? You may think it's easy for
me to just take you in here,

46:50.906 --> 46:53.898
but I ain't the kind of woman who
moves from man to man.

46:54.009 --> 46:57.775
Fact is, it's been quite a while
since I even had anyone to get close to,

46:57.880 --> 46:59.347
you know what I'm saying?

46:59.448 --> 47:01.541
Not that I need a man.
Oh, I need a man like I need a hole

47:01.650 --> 47:04.210
in the goddamn head, but...

47:04.319 --> 47:08.415
I just get lonely sometimes, you know?

47:08.524 --> 47:10.788
It was kind of nice
having somebody around for a change.

47:10.893 --> 47:12.861
It was different.

47:15.831 --> 47:17.765
Oh, you son of a bitch!

48:03.112 --> 48:04.739
I...

48:05.981 --> 48:08.882
Got in some trouble with the Army.

48:11.053 --> 48:15.319
I was stationed at Sakaka
in the Syrian Desert

48:15.424 --> 48:18.393
during the war, and...

48:18.494 --> 48:20.291
These doctors,

48:20.395 --> 48:23.364
they kept coming in
and giving us shots and pills.

48:23.465 --> 48:25.797
A lot of the guys were getting sick

48:25.901 --> 48:30.770
with vomiting, diarrhea,
migraines, black-outs,

48:30.873 --> 48:34.138
and I was having...
I was having some weird thoughts.

48:37.346 --> 48:41.874
And I started feeling sick,
so they shipped me home

48:41.984 --> 48:44.851
and they put me in this hospital
at Groom Lake

48:44.953 --> 48:48.821
and they started running these...
These tests on me.

48:51.226 --> 48:54.889
And they had every kind of doctor
you could imagine just...

48:56.899 --> 48:59.424
Just probing and jabbing at me

48:59.535 --> 49:02.231
and asking me all these weird questions,

49:03.472 --> 49:05.531
feeding me more pills.

49:05.641 --> 49:08.974
Those fucking doctors were
experimenting on me.

49:10.379 --> 49:11.744
I went AWOL.

49:13.382 --> 49:14.679
I was a lifer, too.

49:14.783 --> 49:17.308
I didn't have anywhere to go.

49:17.419 --> 49:18.943
And they don't respond too well

49:19.054 --> 49:21.318
to some drugged-up guinea pig
just taking off.

49:21.423 --> 49:22.913
I don't know...

49:23.792 --> 49:27.421
That I'm not carrying
a disease or a contagion.

49:27.529 --> 49:29.156
Oh, Jesus.

49:30.432 --> 49:31.990
That's how they start.

49:32.100 --> 49:35.228
Typhoid. Legionnaire's disease,
a government screw-up.

49:35.337 --> 49:38.602
AIDS. With the fucking monkeys in Africa.

49:41.310 --> 49:42.902
They're after me.

49:43.812 --> 49:46.303
These people don't fuck around, Agnes.

49:55.991 --> 49:58.653
I shouldn't have told you that,

49:58.760 --> 50:01.354
but I needed to tell somebody.

50:05.534 --> 50:07.468
And I trust you.

50:07.569 --> 50:10.470
I know we haven't known
each other very long.

50:13.575 --> 50:15.543
I don't want to go.

50:24.686 --> 50:26.381
I don't want to go.

50:37.132 --> 50:41.228
Oh, babe, don't leave me. No.

50:45.340 --> 50:48.571
My... Peter.

53:12.721 --> 53:15.155
Can I help you?

53:15.257 --> 53:17.521
Hidy.

53:17.626 --> 53:18.923
No.

53:19.027 --> 53:20.619
Agnes isn't here.

53:21.930 --> 53:23.898
No shit.

53:23.999 --> 53:27.127
- Where is she, Peter?
- The liquor store, I think.

53:33.041 --> 53:35.236
Goddamn, Peter.

53:35.343 --> 53:38.779
I think if I were a roach,
I'd probably take the hint.

53:44.352 --> 53:48.345
- Where's the TV?
- I don't think she has one.

53:48.457 --> 53:50.584
We had one once.

53:50.692 --> 53:53.058
A 19-inch RCA, sure-touch tuning.

53:54.996 --> 53:58.989
I bought it with the money I made
driving a sausage truck.

53:59.100 --> 54:03.298
I drove that truck
20 hours a day sometimes,

54:03.405 --> 54:06.135
just so I could feed my wife and my kid.

54:06.241 --> 54:08.505
You ever do anything like that?

54:10.378 --> 54:12.778
Who the fuck doesn't have a TV?

54:12.881 --> 54:15.441
How are you supposed to know
what's going on in the world, man?

54:15.550 --> 54:19.509
Jesus, we could be invaded
by Martians or some shit, you know?

54:19.621 --> 54:22.647
Fuck, they could be evacuating
the whole goddamn city right now,

54:22.757 --> 54:26.591
and me and you'd be sitting here
with our thumbs up our asses.

54:29.965 --> 54:31.193
Could be.

54:33.068 --> 54:34.695
Who got this stuff out?

54:34.803 --> 54:36.862
I did, for the microscope.

54:43.979 --> 54:45.947
You little shit.

54:47.616 --> 54:48.776
Well...

54:49.818 --> 54:54.118
You might put it back before Aggie gets
home. She ain't gonna like it very much.

54:56.091 --> 54:57.854
What you working on, Peter?

54:57.959 --> 55:00.223
Just looking at something.

55:00.328 --> 55:02.626
Don't touch that, please. I'm...

55:03.965 --> 55:06.433
- I'm looking in...
- What are you looking at?

55:06.535 --> 55:09.663
- A bug.
- Excuse me. A bug?

55:14.676 --> 55:16.667
Just a...

55:16.778 --> 55:18.336
Just a bug?

55:19.981 --> 55:21.881
In my blood.

55:21.983 --> 55:23.883
Oh, in your blood?

55:23.985 --> 55:25.111
Hey...

55:26.421 --> 55:29.481
You know, you remind me of somebody.

55:31.026 --> 55:33.221
You know who you remind me of?

55:34.129 --> 55:37.826
- Do you know who you remind me of?
